Third-party components
----------------------
HydraLab depends on and studies third-party open-source software. Each such
component keeps its own upstream license. The authoritative register of those
dependencies, their SPDX licenses, bundling roles and distribution impact is
ATTRIBUTION.md.

Bundle policy: no strong-copyleft (AGPL/GPL) dependency may appear in any
distributed or packaged build. This is enforced by scripts/license_gate.py and
verified by backend/tests/test_release_pipeline.py against the ATTRIBUTION
register. Copyleft-hazard components (e.g. PyMuPDF, citeproc-js) are
reference-only or optional, non-bundled, subprocess-isolated tools and are
never packaged.

If HydraLab copies or substantially adapts licensed code, the required
copyright notices and license text are preserved at the point of use, per the
license-preservation rule in ATTRIBUTION.md.
